## <a id="overview"></a>Overview

<%= partial vars.path_to_partials + "/ksm/incompatible" %>

To upgrade from <%= vars.product_short %> v<%= previous_version %>:

1. Uninstall <%= vars.product_short %> v<%= previous_version %>.
   See [Uninstall <%= vars.product_short %>](#uninstall) below.

1. Install  <%= vars.product_short %> v<%= current_version %>.
   See [Installing and Configuring <%= vars.product_short %>](./installing.html).

1. Add and enable access to your service offerings. See [Add a Service Offering to <%= vars.product_short %>](./using.html#add)
   and [Enable Service Offering Access](./using.html#enable).

## <a id="uninstall"></a> Uninstall <%= vars.product_short %>

To uninstall <%= vars.product_short %>:

1. View all of your installed releases across all namespaces by running:

    ```
    helm list --all --all-namespaces
    ```
    Record the name of the <%= vars.product_short %> release that you
    want to uninstall.
1. Uninstall <%= vars.product_short %> by running:

    ```
    helm uninstall RELEASE-NAME
    ```
    Where `RELEASE-NAME` is the name of the <%= vars.product_short %>
    release that you recorded in the previous step.
    <br><br>
    For example:

    <pre class="terminal">
    helm uninstall my-<%= vars.product_short.downcase %>-release
    </pre>
